'''''Half-A-Dollar-Bill''''' is a surviving<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lcweb2.loc.gov/diglib/ihas/loc.mbrs.sfdb.565/default.html|title=Half-A-Dollar Bill|date=10 November 2017|website=Lcweb2.loc.gov|accessdate=10 November 2017}}</ref> 1924 American silent [[drama film]] directed by [[W. S. Van Dyke]] and starring [[Anna Q. Nilsson]]. It was produced by an independent company and released through [[Metro Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://silentera.com/PSFL/data/H/HalfADollarBill1924.html|title=Progressive Silent Film List: ''Half-A-Dollar-Bill''|website=silentera.com|accessdate=10 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.afi.com/members/catalog/AbbrView.aspx?s=&Movie=9550|title=Abbreviated View of Movie Page|website=Afi.com|accessdate=10 November 2017}}</ref>

==Cast==
* [[Anna Q. Nilsson]] as The Stranger, Mrs. Webber
* [[William P. Carleton]] as Captain Duncan McTeague
* [[Raymond Hatton]] as Noodles, the cook
* [[Mitchell Lewis]] as Papeete Joe
* [[George MacQuarrie]] as Martin Webber
* [[Frankie Darro]] as Half-A-Dollar-Bill
* Rosa Gore as Gossip

